The paper deals with natural language processing tasks and knowledge bases, which are typically associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of low-dimensional vectors to represent entities and relationships is also a common technique in machine learning and data mining, which suggests the paper could also belong to the databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on link prediction and embedding models suggests it could also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
